with the enemy's leader...

16:35.361 --> 16:36.589
...what would you do?"

16:36.762 --> 16:38.957
Kramer, are these questions
really that important?

16:39.131 --> 16:40.826
Yes, they're important!

16:41.000 --> 16:44.492
If you stumble, if you hesitate,
you can kiss the crown goodbye.

16:44.670 --> 16:49.232
Now, if I told you once, I've told you
a thousand times, poise counts!

16:49.408 --> 16:51.501
It's just as important
as the others.

16:51.677 --> 16:56.478
Swimsuit, eveningwear,
talent, poise!

16:59.485 --> 17:01.851
-Hey. How was the show?
-Good. How was roulette?

17:02.021 --> 17:05.752
I won 50 bucks. This is great.
Too bad Elaine's not here.

17:05.924 --> 17:08.950
Yeah. All she had to do
was buy Mr. Pitt a pair of socks.

17:09.694 --> 17:12.357
-It's good, but--
-But what?

17:12.531 --> 17:16.365
-Ultimately, I don't think they'll stay up.
-No. No, they'll stay up.

17:16.535 --> 17:18.400
For a while, yes,
but not in the long run.

17:18.569 --> 17:20.663
But that's why I got you
the tighter ones.

17:20.839 --> 17:23.433
Forget about those!

17:23.709 --> 17:26.609
-Why do you keep mentioning those?
-What do you want?

17:26.779 --> 17:29.145
I want a decent sock
that's comfortable...

17:29.314 --> 17:30.941
...that will stay on my foot!

17:45.431 --> 17:49.424
-What the hell is that?
-I don't know. It sounds like pigeons.

17:50.169 --> 17:52.535
-Well, I can't sleep with that noise.
-Me either.

17:52.704 --> 17:55.502
Is there anything you can do
to shut them up?

17:55.674 --> 17:57.665
Wait a second.

17:58.610 --> 18:00.771
This will scare them off.

18:11.023 --> 18:13.890
-Well, good night, Ollie.
-Good night, Stan.

18:19.798 --> 18:22.733
-What is it?
-My doves. They're dead.

18:22.901 --> 18:25.062
I trained those birds for eight years.

18:25.237 --> 18:27.262
How am I supposed to do
my magic act now?

18:27.439 --> 18:29.430
-How did this happen?
-They like it outside...

18:29.608 --> 18:31.599
...so I kept them in a cage
on the terrace...

18:31.777 --> 18:34.803
...then I found them dead
in a pool of water.

18:38.684 --> 18:41.847
-But how did this happen?
-It must have been an accident.

18:42.020 --> 18:44.045
Accident?

18:45.290 --> 18:47.656
This was no accident.

18:48.393 --> 18:50.953
These doves were murdered.

18:56.568 --> 18:59.731
Well, that's it.
She's out of the pageant.

19:00.339 --> 19:03.740
-What? Why? What happened?
-Her birds are dead.

19:04.576 --> 19:06.043
-Birds?
-Yeah, birds.

19:06.211 --> 19:08.543
She's got these trained doves.
She does a magic act.

19:08.714 --> 19:11.342
That was her talent for the pageant.

19:11.517 --> 19:15.214
You know what I think, Jerry? I think
somebody murdered those doves.

19:15.787 --> 19:17.880
Somebody wanted her
out of that contest bad.

19:18.056 --> 19:20.456
Somebody who was
just eaten up with jealousy.

19:20.626 --> 19:24.756
Somebody who couldn't stand to have
the spotlight taken off of them.

19:27.833 --> 19:29.494
What are you looking at?

19:32.204 --> 19:33.762
Oh, that. We...

19:33.939 --> 19:36.203
We had to leave that outside
last night...

19:36.375 --> 19:39.936
...because the water
was making the room too cold.

19:41.547 --> 19:43.276
That's...

19:43.849 --> 19:46.113
-You killed them.
-No. You don't understand.

19:46.285 --> 19:48.219
It's not what you think.
It was an accident.

19:48.387 --> 19:51.584
Don't think that you've won, because
you haven't. This kid is a fighter.

19:51.757 --> 19:54.988
And if you think I'm gonna let a couple
of dead birds get in our way...

19:55.160 --> 19:56.957
-...you're crazy!
-Kramer, you gotta--

20:01.200 --> 20:03.691
What was that all about?

20:03.869 --> 20:07.100
Oh, it was just Kramer. Apparently
I killed Miss Rhode Island's doves...

20:07.272 --> 20:09.035
...with the bucket of water
last night.

20:16.648 --> 20:18.912
Ladies and gentlemen,
that was Miss Texas.

20:19.418 --> 20:20.942
Wasn't she wonderful?

20:21.119 --> 20:24.714
And now, continuing with
the talent portion of the competition...

20:24.890 --> 20:27.051
-Okay, this is it.
-How you feeling?

20:27.226 --> 20:30.059
-I'm a little nervous.
-There's nothing to be nervous about.

20:30.229 --> 20:32.891
But I've never sung
before in my life.

20:33.498 --> 20:36.729
And now, let's welcome
Karen Ann Hanson...

20:36.902 --> 20:39.200
...Miss Rhode Island.

21:06.598 --> 21:09.931
I heard those doves
were really incredible.

21:10.102 --> 21:12.161
That's a shame.

21:18.210 --> 21:20.872
It's like watching
an animal get tortured.

21:22.648 --> 21:26.084
-Hey, hey. Yankee game.
-Oh, great. All right.

21:26.251 --> 21:27.809
<i>And the Yankees take the field.</i>

21:27.986 --> 21:31.251
<i>What is with the Yankees? They look
like they're having trouble running.</i>

21:31.423 --> 21:34.449
<i>-They. can't move.
-It's their uniforms. They're too tight.</i>

21:34.626 --> 21:37.595
<i>They've shrunk. They're running
like penguins. Forget this game.</i>

21:37.763 --> 21:41.199
<i>Oh, my. God,
Mattingly. just split his pants.</i>

21:42.301 --> 21:44.496
That's a shame.

21:51.510 --> 21:53.978
Poise. Poise.

22:04.856 --> 22:08.257
The Miss America pageant
seems like a really tough contest.

22:08.427 --> 22:11.760
You come out there in the
bathing suit and the dress shoes.

22:11.930 --> 22:14.228
They got that
sanitized-for-your-protection...

22:14.399 --> 22:17.368
...toilet-seat thing hanging off them,
you know?

22:17.536 --> 22:20.334
Plus, they gotta wear
all the other outfits. I don't know why.

22:20.505 --> 22:22.939
The bathing suit is the contest.

22:23.108 --> 22:25.042
You win the bathing suit, you win.

22:25.210 --> 22:28.407
Everybody looks good in formalwear.
It's dark, it covers everything.

22:28.580 --> 22:30.571
That's why we have weddings in it.

22:30.749 --> 22:32.649
If we had weddings
in bathing suits...

22:32.818 --> 22:34.786
...a lot of ceremonies
wouldn't get past:

22:34.953 --> 22:36.250
"lf anyone sees any reason...

22:36.421 --> 22:39.413
...why these two people
should not be joined together..."

22:39.591 --> 22:42.025
About 80 hands go up.

